Use conditional compilation directives in `MauiProgram.cs` to register the correct implementation per platform:

```csharp
public static MauiApp CreateMauiApp()
{
    var builder = MauiApp.CreateBuilder();
    builder.UseMauiApp<App>();

#if ANDROID
    builder.Services.AddSingleton<INotificationService, Platforms.Android.AndroidNotificationService>();
#elif IOS
    builder.Services.AddSingleton<INotificationService, Platforms.iOS.iOSNotificationService>();
#elif WINDOWS
    builder.Services.AddSingleton<INotificationService, Platforms.Windows.WindowsNotificationService>();
#endif

    return builder.Build();
}
```

Each implementation lives under its respective `Platforms/` folder (which is already per-platform compiled by the SDK). This won't break on any platform because the preprocessor ensures only the relevant registration is compiled for each target.

**Alternative (no `#if`):** Put the registration inside each platform's `Platforms/<OS>/MauiProgram.Platform.cs` partial class, or use the `ConfigureLifecycleEvents` pattern to wire it up per-platform.
